Title: The Earth's Silhouettes
---
What plant can grow if you keep lifting it from the soil?
Let your roots expand unchecked into a vista, a forest, a river, a song,
 or some verse you can hold tenderly.
You need to become quiet for this, as roots work in silence beneath the
 earthâ€™s silhouettes.
Let all your senses extract from me what they can. So mineral-rich I am,
having drawn all a soul ever could from what is above, below and to the side,
 and within us, within us my love.
